news.title: Plans for 100% development fees for areas near Pune metro line
news.para: The changes proposed will impact 23 merged villages near the Metro line where the charges will be 1% instead of 0.5%, while for the interior areas the authority has proposed reduction in charges.

news.title: New home sales in US scale 19-month high as median price drops
news.para: A chronic shortage of previously owned houses is driving buyers to new construction, a situation that builders are taking advantage of by giving a range of incentives to improve affordability.

news.title: Mumbai: Vasai man who posed as builder, cheated prospective buyers arrested
news.para: Sumit Dube’s modus operandi was to advertise the sale of flats in new and old buildings in the Vasai region on social media platforms.

news.title: Chinese asset managers apply to launch first commercial property-backed REITs
news.para: China's securities regulator expanded the REITs scheme to include consumer-related commercial properties, such as shopping malls and department stores, as part of the government's efforts to help the ailing real estate market.

news.title: Gurugram: Nod for boom barriers, gates to four colonies
news.para: The department had received applications from the residents of Brahma City, DLF Pink Town House U block, Sushant Lok 1 A block, Rosewood City A block and Sector 60.

news.title: Noida: 171 GRAP violations, Rs 43 lakh fines issued since October 1
news.para: ​The figures were shared during a review meeting called by Noida Authority's Chief Executive Officer Lokesh M to discuss the compliance of orders issued in the previous meeting.

news.title: ACC posts net profit of Rs 387.88 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: ACC's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 4,644.78 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 14.49 per cent from Rs 4,057.08 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Ganesh Housing Corporation to develop IT SEZ with investment of Rs 8,000 crore in Ahmedabad
news.para: Ganesh Housing Corporation, in collaboration with US real estate development and investment firm Tishman Speyer, the SEZ, called “Million Minds Tech City”, will come up on 65 acres near Chharodi village along SG Road in Ahmedabad.

news.title: Two government offices pay Rs 4 crore property tax to Nashik civic body
news.para: According to NMC officials, the civic body recovered taxes from two offices, including one central government office which has signed an agreement with the NMC saying it would pay service charge instead of property tax.

news.title: Adarsh Developers refinances Rs 3,000 crore debt in two years
news.para: The Bengaluru-based real estate firm plans to invest about Rs 7,000 crore over the next seven years to develop 25 million square feet of residential assets across Bengaluru and enter the plotted development segment, he said.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP told to pay Rs 20,000 to woman accused of property tax default
news.para: On April 16, 2020, HP Sandhya, a resident of Byraveswaranagar on Nagarbhavi Road, remitted property tax of Rs 9,501 to BBMP for her residence for 2019-20 through the online banking option of Canara Bank where she holds an account.

news.title: In a first, Junagadh civic body gets water credits for rainwater harvesting
news.para: The JuMC was issued 9 million water credits for saving one crore litres of water in its Hasnapur water reservoir which meets the city’s 30% demand.

news.title: Delhi: Gujara Construction's director arrested for Rs 2.3 crore property fraud
news.para: According to the police, the accused was identified as 52-year-old Shravan Kumar Chaudhary, a resident of Madhu Vihar in Delhi and the director of Gujara Construction Pvt Ltd.

news.title: PSBs told to speed up sale of defaulters' properties
news.para: State-owned banks regularly issue advertisements listing properties for sale, typically those that have been seized because loans went bad. But the ads usually fly well below the radar of the public. That's set to change.

news.title: Infibeam Group buys Sintex corporate house from NBFC for upto Rs 100 crore
news.para: Infibeam bought the 7,000 square metre plot and 4.20 lakh square feet of constructed property for between Rs 90 crore and Rs 100 crore, sources said.

news.title: NCLT admits insolvency plea against Pune-based Darode Jog Realties
news.para: The tribunal has appointed Akansha Rathi as the insolvency professional to carry out the functions of the company till process is completed.

news.title: Goldman, Warburg sell 'Good Host Spaces' for Rs 2,700 crore to Alta Capital
news.para: Goldman held around 70% in the company that owns and operates third-party purpose-built, on-campus student housing assets across key universities including Manipal University, OP Jindal Global University and Shoolini University.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC issues guidelines to construction industry amid worsening air quality
news.para: The move comes two days after Swiss group IQAir rated Mumbai with an air quality index (AQI) of 160, making it the second most polluted city in the world on Monday, second only to China's Beijing. A score between 151-200 is classed as 'unhealthy', while a score below 100 is 'healthy'.

news.title: Nine illegal colonies in Sultanpur, Bhondsi razed, 35 acres cleared
news.para: District town planner (enforcement) Manish Yadav said a massive demolition drive was carried out in Sultanpur where two illegal colonies, spread over seven acres, were razed by the enforcement wing.

news.title: Preity Zinta buys apartment in Mumbai's Pali Hill for over Rs 17 crore
news.para: Preity Zinta, Bollywood actor and entrepreneur, has purchased a residential apartment in Mumbai's Pali Hill area for over Rs 17 crore. The apartment, located on the 11th floor of an under-construction tower, has a carpet area of 1,474 sq ft. Zinta will also have access to an additional 90 sq ft and two parking slots.
